        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 8 at 5:44PM CDT by NWS Chicago IL</headline>
        <description>At 544 PM CDT/644 PM EDT/, Doppler radar was tracking strong
thunderstorms along a line extending from near Morocco to 6 miles
west of Watseka to 8 miles south of Chatsworth. Movement was east at
40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Onarga, Papineau, Buckley, Martinton, Claytonville, Crescent City,
Earl Park, Cissna Park, Hanging Grove, Brook, Piper City, Woodland,
Foresman, Gilman, Morocco, Beaverville, Remington, Thawville,
Donovan, Milford, Wadena, Mount Ayr, Goodland, Roberts, and Watseka.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead
to localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

These storms may intensify, so be certain to monitor local radio
stations and available television stations for additional information
and possible warnings from the National Weather Service.</instruction>
